Title : Dì sān xiān
Text : '''Dì sān xiān''' ({{zh|地三鲜}}) is a [[Chinese cuisine|Chinese dish]] made of [[Stir frying|stir-fried]] [[potatoes]], [[Eggplant|aubergine/eggplant]], and [[Bell pepper|sweet peppers]].<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=FNFX3BSAUr0C&pg=PA118 Eating Out in China: A Traveler's Resource - Alan Hoenig<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref><ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=IRfi6mvmICsC&pg=PA170 Frommer's Beijing Day by Day - Jen Lin-Liu<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> Other ingredients may include [[garlic]], [[Scallion|spring onion]], etc. The name roughly translates to "three treasures from the earth" because it consists of the three key ingredients listed above.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://omnivorescookbook.com/di-san-xian-recipe/|title=Di San Xian (Fried Potato, Eggplant and Pepper in Garlic Sauce 地三鲜) {{!}} Omnivore's Cookbook|date=2017-03-14|work=Omnivore's Cookbook|access-date=2017-10-27|language=en-US}}</ref> It is a delicacy common in [[North China|northern China]].

